  "prompt": "Why do some emails end in \".edu\"?",
  "response": "Email addresses that end in \".edu\" are typically associated with educational institutions, primarily in the United States. The \".edu\" domain is one of the original top-level domains (TLDs) established in the mid-1980s and is specifically designated for accredited postsecondary institutions, such as universities and colleges. This domain helps signify that the email address is linked to an educational organization. In addition to serving as an identifier, having a \".edu\" email address often grants access to certain academic resources, discounts, and offers that are exclusive to students, faculty, and staff of educational institutions.",
